{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b83ef167-7de8-4899-a989-e9445eb5517f","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` **natively integrates with Microsoft.Testing.Platform**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is **no longer needed** and can be removed. The SDK auto-detects MTP projects (like yours, via `EnableMSTestRunner`).\n\nHere's the cleanup:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_Y4Z79NQKm2jDlYjJ7RhYoL","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_PKIwTPYwLde7a2K5Vr1AdC","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-619e9e204c0f438e898334d2967dc5bc/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-619e9e204c0f438e898334d2967dc5bc/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"44e9e7de-b997-4d1b-9d9f-fece63d09364","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`. They want to know about .NET 10's native MTP support.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. Starting with .NET 10 SDK, the `dotnet test` command uses MTP by default when the test project is an MTP project (i.e., has `EnableMSTestRunner` or similar runner enabled).\n\n\nThe `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is now redundant in .NET 10 since the SDK automatically detects MTP projects, so they can safely remove it from their project file. They'll still need `EnableMSTestRunner` to make the test project an executable that uses MTP, but `dotnet test` will handle the rest natively without any additional configuration.","outputTokens":672,"requestId